Qualifications:
1. 2026 PhD graduate with a background in computer science, network engineering or a related field;
2. Proficiency in at least one programming language, such as Go, C++, or Python, with a strong foundation in designing and developing distributed systems;
3. In-depth understanding of networking protocols and the TCP/IP stack;
4. Practical or research experience in the areas of bandwidth management or distributed rate limiting systems/algorithms will be considered particularly favorable.

